    <title>Foreign Compensation Commission (FCC)</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Foreign Compensation Commission (FCC) is a tribunal established to assess the amount of compensation British claimants are entitled
to under international and British law for losses suffered abroad.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The FCC has also helped in the settlement negotiations of British property losses overseas at the hands of foreign Governments. The FCC report provides a round-up of the Commissionâ€™s judicial duties and administrative functions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
